  "body": "## Issue\r\nIn the Truffle v5 documentation, \"[Interacting with your contracts](https://truffleframework.com/docs/truffle/getting-started/interacting-with-your-contracts#introducing-abstractions)\" describes and links to the truffle-contract module.  In the readme at the link, installation instructions are given:    \r\n      `$ npm install truffle-contract`\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\nExecute `$ npm install truffle-contract`.\r\n\r\n## Actual Results\r\nIf successful, this produces a long set of warnings from recompiling keccak, similar to but much longer than #1584, and then    \r\n       `+ truffle-contract@4.0.0`\r\n\r\nSpecifying version 5 or 5.0.0 results in the package version not being found. \r\n\r\n## Expected Behavior\r\nThere are no errors or warnings, but instead\r\n     `+ truffle-contract@5.0.0`\r\n\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n* Truffle version (`truffle version`): 5.0.0\r\n* node version (`node --version`): 9.3.0\r\n* npm version (`npm --version`): 6.5.0\r\n",
