    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The links and docs are still there, though it's now @truffle/contract.  However, [this comment](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/1587#issuecomment-483363758) seems to explain it, that the `contract` package simply is at a different major version number than the main Truffle package.   Therefore, maintaining the closure makes sense.\r\n\r\nThere is still something actionable though: Adding some documentation somewhere (ideally automatically generated) which shows which version of @truffle/contract (and other packages) correspond to which version of truffle could be helpful. My strategy to get the information in the absence of that documentation involves digging through the GitHub commit history to find the commit at which version numbers were updated and look at the other package version numbers as of the same commit.  ",
